<Layout title="Session 114 — Tales of the Radiant Citadel" description="The party fought their way back through hallways now choked with grey-green hybrid ooze to clean out the lab before it collapsed. Kiet picked up the **plan">
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
    <a href="/studio" class="text-sm text-earth hover:text-ink transition-colors mb-6 inline-block">&larr; Studio</a>

    <h1 class="font-heading text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black leading-tight mb-2">
      Session 114
    </h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-earth mb-1">Tales of the Radiant Citadel &middot; May 19, 2026</p>
    <p class="text-sm text-ink-light mb-8">Bluetspur Expedition</p>

    <div class="prose-section text-ink-light leading-relaxed mb-12 space-y-4">
      <p>
        The party fought their way back through hallways now choked with grey-green hybrid ooze to clean out the lab before it collapsed. Kiet picked up the **plane-tearing shard** at the center of the irradiated chamber — and **nicked the universe** doing it (the shard tears space-time when moved, &quot;the universe will bleed&quot;). The party finished the lab's guardian (a memory-eating ooze that hit Sundr for **41 psychic damage** on a botched wisdom save) and the moment it died, **everyone's stolen memories rushed back at once** and the building started aging into dust around them. With minutes before collapse, the party split up and looted three more weapons projects: **Toven** scored the three **Disjunction Gems** (mutually repelling magnets that, if ever bonded, become a 300-ft anti-magic null field — Sam confirmed this is the D&amp;D-movie helm) and a jar of **Illithid mucus** (Psychic Reservoir, unprocessed); **Virgil** stocked up on **six Rage Stones** from the Resident Stones storage and got hit by a cabinet of *ennui* on his way out (&quot;I don't even know what ennui is&quot; — he leaves the room because emotions are weakness); **Haru** collected **two petrified Elder Brain Dragon eggs** into the portable hole; and **Sundr** went to the Bad Thought chamber, jammed the cable straight into his own head, and **downloaded the recursive philosophy that kills mind flayers into his brain**. The Bad Thought's parting message: *&quot;Complete the mission. All you must do now is have your brain be eaten by a mind flayer.&quot;* Sundr (Erik): &quot;Ah, he's being metaphorical. Let's do it.&quot; Long rest in the now-quiet petrified forest (the green skeletons collapsed when the lab died), Toven Identified everything, Toven created water for Kiet's mutant intake, and Twelve crawled up to Sundr to ask what it feels like to carry one of the greatest thoughts ever thought. Next session: low-flying assault on Sauron — the god brain's lair, NW.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Highlights</h2>
    <ul class="text-sm text-ink-light leading-relaxed space-y-2 mb-12 list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Sundr Leaps the Console &quot;For the Gram&quot;</strong> — Combat picked back up from session 113's end. Hallway full of hybrid grey-green oozes, lined up sunbeam-style. Sundr (Erik): **&quot;Let's do it for the gram, my brother. This is gonna be a good picture.&quot;**</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Kiet Picks Up the Universe — and Nicks It</strong> — Inside the now-quiet inner chamber, Kiet investigates the **plane-tearing shard** floating at the table center. Arcana check stacked with all his exhaustion penalties; final result 17.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Kiet's Plane-Vision Orbs — Two New Worlds</strong> — The orbs around the chamber show different worlds. Kiet detaches/disconnects from one at a time:</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Sundr Drops Wall of Fire on the Hallway</strong> — The hybrid oozes try to porridge their way down the hallway toward Sundr. He is **flying** (Heavenly Wings), so they cannot tag him on the way past.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Sundr's Chromatic Orb — Take Two — &quot;Pillar of the Ooze Community&quot;</strong> — A taller pillar-of-merged-ooze rears up at Sundr. He casts **Chromatic Orb** again, but rolls a 13 — miss.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Haru's Cacophonous Shield Lawn-Mower</strong> — **Cacophonous Shield activates** — 10 ft radius persistent damage aura around Haru. Anything inside takes Con-save or get blasted. Sam: &quot;Constitution saving throws. Bam. That's a failure. That's a failure, and that's a failure.&quot;</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Toven's Spectral Wolves Continue Earning Their Keep</strong> — Toven keeps the spectral wolf pack moving — wolves auto-3d10 aura damage to any ooze within 10 ft. Hallway crowded to the point that the wolves can't reach the front line; he holds back, lobs **Fireball** when Kiet hits the hybrid guardian later.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Virgil Opens the Doors</strong> — Virgil drives the entire room-clearing phase as **the keycard holder.** Cuts through the hallway oozes effortlessly (still in rage; &quot;You're not even in that rage for you. You're just like, ugh&quot;), then sprints door to door with the scientist keycard.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">The Memory-Eater — 41 Psychic Damage, Then the Memories Rush Back</strong> — A grey-and-white **hybrid ooze** in the corner is the lab's **last guardian.** It's been hiding, holding the party's stolen memories.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">The Final Sprint — Four Rooms, Minutes Before Collapse</strong> — Console + lab + table with **three jewel-like stones, magnetic in some uncanny way.** Hold two near each other, fine; introduce a third and **all three scatter.**</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">The Bad Thought — Sundr Plugs Himself In</strong> — The Bad Thought room: **&quot;You feel as if you are inside of a mechanical brain. It is ominous. It is humming with the last dying vestiges. This will die soon, and the Bad Thought will die with it as the energy leaves this building.&quot;**</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Exfil — and the Lab Dies</strong> — No time to bust through the ceiling. Party sprints back through the hallways with Virgil keycarding the way out. The lab **slumps behind them** as they emerge.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">The Long Rest — Twelve and the Bad Thought</strong> — Toven casts **Create Water (1st level)** into a giant jug to keep Kiet hydrated through the night (his mutation tripled his water needs).</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Status Effects at Session End</strong> — **Sundr:** Permanent **Bad Thought** carrier. Sam framed it as glitchy / Tourettes-like external signs (&quot;Sunder is glitching&quot;). Erik's note: *full of mind virus, now has Tourettes-like symptoms.*</li>
      <li><strong class="text-ink">Schedule Note</strong> — Sam: **Two more Tuesdays before he goes on vacation.** Need to talk summer scheduling.</li>
    </ul>

